    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i keep getting a MemoryError when i try to run this script that processes a huge csv file with pandas. i think it's because i'm loading the whole thing at once. what's the actual difference between using a list comprehension vs a generator function for handling these rows? i need to keep the memory usage low.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A **list comprehension** builds the entire collection in memory at once, like a big, overflowing pile of things. A **generator function**, on the other hand, is like a little pipe, only producing one item at a time when you ask for it. This is crucial when dealing with massive CSVs, because a generator keeps the memory footprint tiny, just enough space for the current piece of data. If you load the whole CSV into a list, it's like trying to stuff a whole mountain of gravel into a tiny pocket—it just won't fit!",
      "source": "target",
